fetch Google Flu Trends data

Source: R/endpoints.R
gft.Rd

Obtains estimates of inluenza activity based on volume of certain search queries from Google.

gft(locations, epiweeks)

Arguments

locations

A character string that specifies a location to be fetched.

epiweeks

Takes in the form epirange(startdate,enddate), where startdate and enddate are of the form YYYYMMDD (can be passed as string or numeric).

Value

an instance of epidata_call

Details

Google has discontinues Flu Trends, and this is now a static endpoint. Possibile input for locations can be found in https://github.com/cmu-delphi/delphi-epidata/blob/main/labels/regions.txt, https://github.com/cmu-delphi/delphi-epidata/blob/main/labels/states.txt, and https://github.com/cmu-delphi/delphi-epidata/blob/main/labels/cities.txt.

References

API Documentation: https://cmu-delphi.github.io/delphi-epidata/api/gft.html

Examples

call <- gft(locations = "hhs1", epiweeks = epirange(201201, 202001))
fetch_classic(call)
